        "markdown": "## Task\n\nDefine the **Task** node type.\n\nQuestions to answer:\n- What makes a task atomic enough for implementation use?\n- Should tasks carry status, owner, priority, or estimate?\n- How should tasks connect to goals, dependencies, and acceptance criteria?\n- Do tasks map directly to execution prompts?\n\nOutput:\n- task scope rules\n- canonical data shape\n- execution linkage",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "_classBinding": {
